OL,3,CTeenager's life 'could have been
OL,4,Csaved' after asthma attack
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Ms Hassell also raised
OL,7,Fconcerns about "safety-netting" - a
OL,8,Fterm used when information is given to
OL,9,Fa patient or their carer during a
OL,10,Fprimary care consultation, about
OL,11,Factions to take if their condition
OL,12,Ffails to improve .
OL,14,FShe wrote: "Billie was safety-netted
OL,15,Fwhen she was discharged. Her parents
OL,16,Fwere told to bring her back if they
OL,17,Fhad any concerns.
OL,26,@oD@POUoD@_O]vD@LOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/11
